# API Layer Rules

## Before Modifying API Code

1. Read /docs/development/API_CONTRACTS.md for existing endpoints
2. Check /docs/architecture/DATABASE_SCHEMA.md for data models
3. Review /docs/architecture/AUTH_SYSTEM.md for auth requirements

## API Structure

- Each resource gets its own file (e.g., `events.ts`, `users.ts`)
- Export typed functions, not raw fetch calls
- Handle errors consistently using shared error types
- Include TypeScript types for all request/response shapes

## Naming Conventions

- Functions: verbNoun (e.g., `getEvents`, `createEvent`, `updateEvent`)
- Types: PascalCase (e.g., `EventResponse`, `CreateEventRequest`)
